spec: concurrent_futures_extra65
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#inspect — Python function __kwdefaults__ documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends concurrent_futures_extra64.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __name__/__module__/__qualname__, CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor/InvalidStateError identity and bases, as_completed/wait __name__/__qualname__, FIRST_COMPLETED/FIRST_EXCEPTION/ALL_COMPLETED values and __len__(), class __module__/__name__/__len__() tables, submit/shutdown qualname lens, Future method qualname lens, class __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables, wait/__name__=='wait', as_completed/__name__=='as_completed', wait/__qualname__.__len__()==4, as_completed/__qualname__.__len__()==12, class __class__.__name__/__qualname__ equality, wait/__class__.__module__=='builtins' and ThreadPoolExecutor/__class__.__module__=='builtins', class __doc__/__class__/__module__=='builtins' tables, ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'), as_completed/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'), ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future __init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function'), class __repr__/__weakref__ __class__.__name__ tables, exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ tables, cf.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list'), cf.__all__.__len__()==14, __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'), cf.__all__.__contains__ membership checks, cf.__package__.__eq__('concurrent.futures'), Future/Executor __doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str'), __loader__/__spec__/__file__/__cached__ __class__.__name__, __spec__ attributes, Future/__init__ and ThreadPoolExecutor/__init__ and Future.result/done/cancel/exception and ThreadPoolExecutor.submit/shutdown __qualname__.__eq__, wait/as_completed __annotations__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict'), wait __globals__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict'), wait __globals__.__contains__('wait'), Future.__doc__.__contains__('Represents'), ThreadPoolExecutor.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') (extra59), wait/__defaults__/__code__/__class__.__name__ checks, as_completed/__defaults__/__code__/__class__.__name__ checks, Future.__init__/__defaults__/__class__.__name__ checks (extra60), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ __code__.co_name equality and co_argcount values (extra61), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ co_varnames/co_filename/co_flags attribute chains (extra62), wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ co_consts/co_nlocals/co_stacksize type identity (extra63), wait/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='tuple', wait/__defaults__.__len__()==2, as_completed/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='tuple', as_completed/__defaults__.__len__()==1, Future.__init__/__defaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType', executor __class__.__name__=='type' (extra64)."
    - "This spec covers (cfkw65 namespace): wave 234 theme — __kwdefaults__ NoneType identity for wait/as_completed/Future.__init__; ThreadPoolExecutor/__module__/__qualname__/__name__ string equality; ProcessPoolExecutor/__module__/__qualname__/__name__ string equality; Executor/__module__/__qualname__/__name__ string equality; Future/__module__/__name__ string equality. NEW in extra65: wait.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType'; as_completed.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType'; Future.__init__.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__=='NoneType'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__=='ThreadPoolExecutor'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.thread'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__qualname__=='ThreadPoolExecutor'; ProcessPoolExecutor.__name__=='ProcessPoolExecutor'; ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.process'; ProcessPoolExecutor.__qualname__=='ProcessPoolExecutor'; Executor.__name__=='Executor'; Executor.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; Executor.__qualname__=='Executor'; Future.__name__=='Future'; Future.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'."
    - "concurrent.futures.wait.__kwdefaults__ is None. wait(fs, timeout=None, return_when=ALL_COMPLETED) has all positional-or-keyword parameters; no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.as_completed.__kwdefaults__ is None. as_completed(fs, timeout=None) has all positional-or-keyword parameters; no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__init__.__kwdefaults__ is None. Future.__init__(self) has no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures.thread'. ThreadPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py which sets __name__ to 'concurrent.futures.thread'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures.process'. ProcessPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py which sets __name__ to 'concurrent.futures.process'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Executor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. Executor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py which sets __name__ to 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. Future is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py which sets __name__ to 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures __kwdefaults__ NoneType checks — extra65
#
# Wave 234 theme: __kwdefaults__ NoneType identity.
#
# wait(fs, timeout=None, return_when=ALL_COMPLETED) has all positional-or-keyword
# parameters; no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None.
# as_completed(fs, timeout=None) has all positional-or-keyword parameters;
# no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None.
# Future.__init__(self) has no keyword-only parameters. __kwdefaults__ is None.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra65.none_kwdefaults:
  description: "concurrent.futures wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') checks in cfkw65 namespace — wave 234 theme: __kwdefaults__ NoneType identity; wait/as_completed/Future.__init__ have no keyword-only parameters; __kwdefaults__ is None for all; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra65: first __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') checks for these functions in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: kwdefaults
  id_prefix: cfkw65

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [wait_kwdefaults_class,          wait.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,           ["NoneType"], true, "wait.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — wait(fs, timeout=None, return_when=ALL_COMPLETED) has all positional-or-keyword parameters with no keyword-only parameters; __kwdefaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra65: first __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for wait in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [as_completed_kwdefaults_class,  as_completed.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,   ["NoneType"], true, "as_completed.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — as_completed(fs, timeout=None) has all positional-or-keyword parameters with no keyword-only parameters; __kwdefaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra65: first __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for as_completed in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [future_init_kwdefaults_class,   Future.__init__.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["NoneType"], true, "Future.__init__.__kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — Future.__init__(self) has no keyword-only parameters; __kwdefaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra65: first __kwdefaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for Future.__init__ in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures ThreadPoolExecutor identity checks — extra65
#
# Wave 234 theme: ThreadPoolExecutor class identity.
#
# ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__ == 'ThreadPoolExecutor'
# ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures.thread'
# ThreadPoolExecutor.__qualname__ == 'ThreadPoolExecutor'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra65.ThreadPoolExecutor_identity:
  description: "concurrent.futures ThreadPoolExecutor class identity checks in cfkw65 namespace — wave 234 theme: ThreadPoolExecutor identity; ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__=='ThreadPoolExecutor'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.thread' (defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py); ThreadPoolExecutor.__qualname__=='ThreadPoolExecutor'; NEW in extra65: first __name__/__module__/__qualname__ string equality checks for ThreadPoolExecutor in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: cfkw65a

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [tpe_name,     ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__.__eq__,     ["ThreadPoolExecutor"],        true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__name__ == 'ThreadPoolExecutor' — ThreadPoolExecutor is a top-level class; its __name__ attribute is the simple class name 'ThreadPoolExecutor'; NEW in extra65: first __name__.__eq__ check for ThreadPoolExecutor in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [tpe_module,   ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__.__eq__,   ["concurrent.futures.thread"], true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures.thread' — ThreadPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py; the module sets its __name__ to 'concurrent.futures.thread'; ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__ is 'concurrent.futures.thread'; NEW in extra65: first __module__.__eq__ check for ThreadPoolExecutor in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [tpe_qualname, ThreadPoolExecutor.__qualname__.__eq__, ["ThreadPoolExecutor"],        true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__qualname__ == 'ThreadPoolExecutor' — ThreadPoolExecutor is a top-level class in concurrent.futures.thread; its qualified name is simply 'ThreadPoolExecutor'; __qualname__.__eq__('ThreadPoolExecutor') returns True; NEW in extra65: first __qualname__.__eq__ check for ThreadPoolExecutor in the cfkw65 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures ProcessPoolExecutor identity checks — extra65
#
# Wave 234 theme: ProcessPoolExecutor class identity.
#
# ProcessPoolExecutor.__name__ == 'ProcessPoolExecutor'
